{"key":"post-8514740","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>8514740</id>\n<content>The dish soap is a wetting agent that also helps pasteurize the straw.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You'll want to add some verm to your mix to prevent the bagged cow manure from turning to mud.&amp;nbsp; In fact, I'd mix the manure and verm together before adding to the straw.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Don't use lime in substrate.&amp;nbsp; Mushroom mycelium prefers a slightly acidic substrate.&amp;nbsp; Lime is for casing mix.&amp;nbsp; I'd also leave the oil out, or at least cut the amount in half.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>8514993</next>\n<prev>8514291</prev>\n<first>8513375</first>\n<last>8514993</last>\n<when>1213287940</when>\n<utime>06/12/08 07:25 PM</utime>\n</post>"}